{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Smart Tool + Prompt Combo\n      A get_design_context tool that the AI calls before generating UI code. It fetches tokens + components + patterns, applies intelligent compression (only relevant tokens for the task), and returns a tailored context block. Paired with an MCP prompt template use-design-system that the user can invoke.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            Context is task-aware — returns only relevant tokens/components\n            Prompt template gives users a one-command trigger\n            Tool can cache internally + compress intelligently\n            Works naturally with \"smart detection\" — AI decides when to call\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Relies on the AI deciding to call the tool (may forget)\n            More logic in the compression/relevance filtering\n            Prompt templates have limited client support currently","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1773476310991}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"B\n    \n      Layered Resources + Cache\n      Multiple resources at different granularity — designsystem://tokens/{fileKey}, designsystem://components/{fileKey}, designsystem://patterns/{fileKey}, designsystem://rules/{fileKey}. An in-memory cache avoids repeated Figma API calls. A build_design_context tool pre-warms the cache and returns a compact summary.\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            AI can read only what it needs per task\n            Cache makes repeated reads instant\n            Smart detection tool can decide which resources to read\n            Each resource stays within reasonable context size\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            More complex — multiple resources to coordinate\n            Cache invalidation needs thought (TTL? manual refresh?)\n            AI must know which resources to read and when","choice":"b","id":null,"timestamp":1773476320522}
